Bertoxx</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=calidainstormheart>Calidain Stormheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Local user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>3/20/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>9:40:08 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Vermilion, you missed his point completely......</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">in that there are no weapons that drop from either Dragons or Gods that a Paladin can use.  Those weapons you listed, while they may end up being awesome, they are quest items out of the Plane of Sky.  All the weapons he listed drop off the Dragon or God as soon as you kill him, Paladins have to quest for all our items.<br>
