</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ugramosk.showPublicProfile>Gramosk</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>3/20/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>10:28:53 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://succoringwinds.dynhost.com/Character_Image_Thumbs/gramosk_face1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Vermilion, you missed his point completely......</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">He also missed the reason they aren't doable until the expansion. They aren't because no one is high enough right now to get far enough in to sky. In a month when expansion comes out, you'll have a whole bunch of people level 51 (assuming that those that have a full exp bar the day before expansion still have a full exp bar after expansion hits.) It might be that we need to be level 53 or 55 or whatever level it takes to kill the boss and get farther in sky. And for that, it might be several weeks or more before there are many raids that go farther in sky. (Another thing that is going to happen is that people aren't going to be so eager to go to the plane and die multiple times when they no longer have maxed out experience.)<br>
<br>
The point of this thread is that paladins don't have any weapons that drop off dragons or gods (other than a 2 handed staff on vox which paladins &quot;can&quot; use, but why any paladin would want to, I don't know.) We have Fiery Avenger which requires 2 dragon drops and much more work than simply killing a god and looting a no drop weapon off it.<br>
<br>
It should tell you something when you consider that the best two hander a paladin can use other than fiery avenger is a rare drop off a fire giant. This weapon can be used by both shadow knights and warriors, but both have several options better than it. We do have a sprinkler (if it ever stops dropping again) but, while this is a good upgrade ratio wise to ghoulbane, it isn't really a dragon or god quality weapon.<br>
</font><P>Gramosk Elarvie'Siil<BR>
